CNMV has also announced that this offer aims at the acquisition of 550.008 shares of Federico Paternina at the price of 7,65 Euro per share, which in turn represents 8,95 % of the company's capital, which is composed of 6,142,786 euros in shares approved on the Madrid and Bilbao stock exchanges.
In addition, it has been announced that 5.592.778 million shares have been fixed, which can in no way be transferred until the conclusion of the tender and whose price has been fixed by Federico Paternina in accordance with the laws of law.
