Every day thousands of vehicles involved in an accident are dragged into the workshops, where a assessor has to assess the damage caused and the costs of repair.
No accident is the same, and calculating the cost of parts and hours of work can be a long and complicated task.
The calculation of the repair costs of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros per hand, including parts and working hours, may take up to two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the support of the latest IT tools, it is a matter of minutes
Therefore, almost 100 % of the assessors use this type of system.
The service and application providers for the assessment of accidents and repairs collect the information they receive from the manufacturers to process them afterwards and provide them to their customers in the form of a useful program.
In Spain, Audatex, part of the American group Solera, is the market leader; 80% of all opinions are produced with their products.
The other two companies competing with the tool market for assessment and preparation of a report are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data provided by the manufacturers is anything but easy.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, Sales Manager of Audatex, 63 manufacturers and importers are working together, each of which provides the information in a different format.
In addition, the volume of data to be processed is becoming greater and larger, to the point that over the last five years even more versions, variants and motorizations have come on the market than over the entire fifteen years before.
As soon as a new car enters the market, the company starts working.
It is a laborious task, because each of the thousands of vehicles must be catagolized and their price entered.
In addition, each model creates an "intelligent" graphic image that allows you to "click on" different parts of the vehicle.
In the case of a much-sold model, work can be completed in one week if the procedure progresses quickly.
In the case of a less common car, it may take up to three or four months. At present, Audatex has a total of 99.2% of the cars sold in Spain.
Among the more exclusive models, they have information about Porsche models, but not about Ferrari or Lamborghini.
With regard to the vehicle park running on the roads, it is over 99%.
For the purposes of carrying out documentation and the production of databases, Audatex has eight centers distributed worldwide (Spain, France, Germany, the USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them has specialized in certain brands.
The national headquarters is located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There more than one hundred technicians (usually mechanics) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests 90 million euros a year in the preparation of these databases.
Every month they collect 2.5 million data and their customers receive the updates every second day.
The development of this enormous flow of information enables companies to use it in different ways and thus to offer different products.
The most common use is the use for repairs and repairs, but, depending on the country, there are also tools for the management of scrap parts or for calculating the loss or residual value of a car.
The only company that informs about the value of the used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer this offer in Spain, but in the United States.
When looking through the products that Audatex offers, you can easily get an overview of the type of support it provides to industry experts.
