The workshop's cost estimate in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, the company Audatex ensures that the user receives a cost suggestion in just four steps: identification of the vehicle, search of the spare part, creation and creation of a cost suggestion.
The easy handling of these systems is a basic condition, especially in order to convince older professionals who are usually more or less opposed to the use of these new computer techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger vehicles, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 small transporters and 44 trucks.
Of course, you need to use a computer with Internet connection.
After the model to be repaired has been identified using the chassis number, a graphic of the respective model appears and then the required spare part is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price for working hours, surcharges or discounts and then print out the cost estimate and pass it on to his customers.
However, AudaTaller is not a tool to assess such as AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalog.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop does not include estimated hours.
The cost of using this tool is 350 euros a year, an amount which the customer can pay without further delay.
The company Audatex is currently working on being able to offer these images in three-dimensional formats.
This is an innovation that automechanics have been waiting for a long time, for example, because you can select a door with it and then you can turn the picture completely to look at the inside.
